%I A397482 #7 Jul 03 2026 23:01:32
%S A397482 46,94,946,1139,31143
%N A397482 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)^4*psi(x) = x^5 + y^5 + z^5 + t^5 + w^5.
%C A397482 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma^4*psi-quintic quintuple.
%H A397482 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A397482 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-4-psi-quintic-quintuples/blob/main/A397482">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397482 (94, 38, 86, 92, 134) is such a quintuple because sigma(94)^4 * psi(94) = 144^4 * 144 = 94^5 + 38^5 + 86^5 + 92^5 + 134^5.
%o A397482 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A397482 Cf. A000203, A001615, A003350, A386672, A390006, A395737, A397058, A397060.
%K A397482 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A397482 1,1
